class Solution {
public:
    string defangIPaddr(string address) {
        for (int i = 0; i < address.size(); i++) {
            if (address[i] == '.') {
                address.replace(i, 1, "[.]");
                i += 2;
            }
        }
        return address;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
explanation: The solution iterates through the input string, replacing each '.' with '[.]'. It adjusts the index after replacement to account for the increased length, ensuring all '.' are processed correctly.

